node.text: When it's too hot out to turn on your oven, the time is right to experience the phenomenal crisp texture and flavor of grilled pizza. Happy Pride Month! Watch how the King Arthur Baking community is kicking off celebrations. ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜

"We celebrate Pride because we are committed to a more diverse and inclusive future — and we want to show up for each other." - Karen Colberg, King Arthur Baking co-CEO

King Arthur Baking Company is making a donation to @TheTrevorProject, which provides crisis intervention and suicide prevention services to lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, queer & questioning (LGBTQ) young people under 25. We encourage you to learn more and donate at bakewith.us/TrevorProject

node.title: Celebrate Pride With Us - King Arthur Baking Company - Pride 2021

node.text: These Perfectly Pillowy Cinnamon Rolls need to get rolling! Bake our 2021 #recipeoftheyear today: bakewith.us/ROTY2021

node.accessibility_caption: Some perfect no bake make at home Almond Joy candies on a plate. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: A collection of no-bake recipes so you can keep the oven off during the summer heat? Now that’s a cause for (almond) joy! Including these chocolaty-coconut-almond treats, you’ll find frozen desserts, cheesecakes, small bites, pies, and even bread pudding that can all be made without your oven. Find the collection and this Coconut-Almond Candies recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your no-bake favorites with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A trimmed and docked tart crust in a round pan, ready for baking. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Pâte Sucrée is no one-trick pony in the pastry world. This enriched dough creates a lightly sweet flavor and pleasantly crumbly texture (not unlike shortbread), and is ideal for fruit tarts, sweet pastries, and can even be rolled into cookies. Use our #GlutenFree Measure for Measure Flour if you need to bake GF! Find this NEW recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share what you make with your batch of pâte sucrée with #KingArthurBaking.

node.accessibility_caption: A plate with a hearty carrot muffin cut in half with apricot jam spread on one of the halves. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: A hearty and wholesome way to start your day, one of the smash hits in our Norwich, Vermont bakery is now available on our website! Packed with goodies like carrots, banana, nuts, flax, and more, you can take a little trip to Vermont for this #vegan treat without leaving your kitchen. (You should totally come visit us, though. We have cookies!) Find this recipe linked in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your batch of our bakery’s vegan muffins with #KingArthurBaking.

node.accessibility_caption: A stack of Blini, yeast-raised buckwheat pancakes, topped with sour cream, smoked salmon, and capers. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text: Packing a punch of flavor in both sweet and savory recipes, buckwheat is a naturally #GlutenFree grain we’ve been reaching for to amp up recipes such as brownies, pancakes, Stromboli, and more! Read up on our guide to baking with buckwheat at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your buckwheat bakes with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A rustic mixed berry pie in a metal pie plate with two scoops of ice cream placed in the middle of the pie. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text: Without gorgeous berries, tender shortcake, frozen treats, and fruit pies for days, this season would be more like a bummer, not a summer. Featuring recipes that highlight summer produce (and a few nostalgic hits thrown in too), our Classic Summer Desserts collection is ready for you to rediscover an old favorite. Find it at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking along with this recipe for Mixed Berry Pie, and share your bakes with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: Three small stacks of cookies on a cooling rack. -Photo by King Arthur Baking

node.text: Don’t let their simple appearance deter you — you do NOT want to miss out on a batch of these Sweet Corn Cookies! (@chefsusaninvt even turned hers into ice cream sandwiches!) Inspired by a recipe from @christinatosi and made with cornmeal and masa harina, these soft and chewy sugar cookies are sweet, salty, and reminiscent of the crunchy corn breakfast cereal so many of us grew up with. Find this NEW recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your batch with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A slice of cake with three layers of cake and buttercream between the layers. -Photo by King Arthur Baking

node.text: Buttercream … without butter? With plant-based butters, it can be done! We’re putting two of the most popular vegan butters to the test with butter-heavy recipes to see how they perform. See the results (including which type of butter went into each layer of this cake!) at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your plant-based bakes with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A slice of cake with three layers of cake and buttercream between the layers. -Photo by King Arthur Baking
An overhead shot of various vegan butter alternatives, including the brands, Earth Balance and Miyoko’s. -Photo by King Arthur Baking
A pie plate with half of a peach pie with a lattice top remaining and three forks resting in the pan. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text: Without a peeler, knife, or frustration, you can perfectly peel dozens of peaches in just a few minutes, making cobblers, pies, shortcakes, and more all that much closer to being in your belly. Is it wizardry? No, it’s our own PJ (who really is pretty magical), and she’s here with a quick, easy tip for peeling peaches in a flash. Tap the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking to see how, and show us your peachy bakes with #KingArthurBaking
